  FFmpeg and ffprobe — version 8.1, unmodified upstream binaries.
  Copyright (c) the FFmpeg developers.

  The license of the bundled FFmpeg build depends on the platform:

    - Windows (x86_64 and ARM64): GNU Lesser General Public License,
      version 2.1 or later (LGPL-2.1-or-later). BtbN "lgpl" build, configured
      WITHOUT --enable-gpl / --enable-nonfree (excludes libx264 / libx265).

    - macOS (arm64 and x86_64): GNU General Public License, version 3 or later
      (GPL-3.0-or-later). ffmpeg.martin-riedl.de build, configured WITH
      --enable-gpl (includes libx264 / libx265). EasyClip performs lossless
      stream copy only ("-c copy") and never uses these encoders, but the
      binary shipped on macOS is nonetheless GPL-licensed.

  Corresponding source: the complete corresponding source code for the exact
  bundled FFmpeg 8.1 build — including every GPL-covered component — is
  available from https://ffmpeg.org/download.html together with the build
  projects that produced the binaries:
    - Windows: https://github.com/BtbN/FFmpeg-Builds
    - macOS:   https://ffmpeg.martin-riedl.de/
  Written offer: for three (3) years from the date of distribution, you may
  obtain the complete corresponding source for any bundled FFmpeg build by
  opening an issue at https://github.com/lifebugz/easyclip; it will be provided
  (or a download location given) at no more than the cost of distribution.
  The exact builds and SHA-256 checksums are pinned in
  scripts/ffmpeg-checksums.json; the Windows LGPL archives are additionally
  mirrored at https://github.com/lifebugz/easyclip/releases.

  Replace right: because FFmpeg is shipped as a separate executable, you may run
  a modified FFmpeg by replacing the sidecar binary at
  src-tauri/binaries/ffmpeg-<target-triple> (or the corresponding file inside
  the installed application bundle) with your own compatible build. (This is
  required by the LGPL for the Windows build, and is offered for all platforms.)

Full third-party license texts — the GNU LGPL v2.1 (Windows sidecar) and the
